{
  "texts": [
    "Conv-AttentionFor self-attention, the input is represented as n d-dimensional vectors x, which constitute X = (x 1, x 2..., x n), and the specific operation can be represented asQ = X W Q, K = X W K, V = X W V where Q, K, Vare denoted as key, query and value, and W Q, W K, W V represents the fully connected layer parameters.",
    "The attention matrix in self-attention is represented asa matrix A = so f t max( Q K T √ d k) of n × n, the output can be represented asX i = n j=1 A i j V j.In contrast to Eq. 1, the attention matrix A i j is obtained similarly to the symbolic function α k (x i) in VLAD.",
    "In VLAD, the symbolic function α k (x i) is determined based on the relationship between descriptors and clustering centers.",
    "In self-attention, the attention matrix A i j is determined by the relationship between key and query.",
    "Thus, we can also consider query as a descriptor for the vector to be queried, and key as a place to be queried, and the relationship between the two as descriptors and clustering centers."
  ]
}